1
00:00:03,540 --> 00:00:06,700
In the lives of servitors

2
00:00:06,700 --> 00:00:13,370
we have to also deal 
with our past or …

3
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:17,000
what’s sometimes called 
prārabdha-karma.

4
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:21,586
[Conventional Suffering | 
Escaping Illusion]

5
00:00:21,766 --> 00:00:25,066
The karma that you are stuck with
in this life, that you generated.

6
00:00:25,066 --> 00:00:28,446
We generated 
this particular body

7
00:00:28,446 --> 00:00:30,423
and karmic
circumstances

8
00:00:30,423 --> 00:00:36,693
before coming in connection
with Kṛṣṇa consciousness.

9
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:44,523
So it has so much 
karmic destiny in play.

10
00:00:45,900 --> 00:00:50,100
Then someone comes in connection 
with Kṛṣṇa consciousness.

11
00:00:50,100 --> 00:00:53,900
Rūpa Gosvāmī says 
in Bhakti-rasāmṛta-sindhu,

12
00:00:53,900 --> 00:00:57,066
kleśa-ghnī śubha-dā mokṣa-
laghutā-kṛt su-durlabhā

13
00:00:57,066 --> 00:01:01,416
sāndrānanda-viśeṣātmā
śrī-kṛṣṇākarṣiṇī ca sā
[Brs: 1.1.17]

14
00:01:01,416 --> 00:01:06,163
He’s outlining 
what is kṛṣṇa-bhakti substantially,

15
00:01:06,163 --> 00:01:09,033
and what is the outcome

16
00:01:09,033 --> 00:01:13,073
or what are symptoms, 
what are side-effects,

17
00:01:13,073 --> 00:01:13,983
what is the outcome.

18
00:01:13,983 --> 00:01:16,833
Everything is being taken
into consideration

19
00:01:16,833 --> 00:01:18,933
beginning with kleśa-ghnī.

20
00:01:18,933 --> 00:01:22,133
Saying, the suffering,

21
00:01:22,133 --> 00:01:25,000
the conventional
suffering that’s associated

22
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:27,800
with being embodied, 
prārabdha-karma,

23
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:29,700
your accumulated karma 
in this life,

24
00:01:29,700 --> 00:01:32,800
he says, 
“It will put an end to that.”

25
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:38,000
Now, people will think,
“Oh, but what we see, you know ...

26
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:40,100
Devotees are suffering
in different ways.”

27
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:44,586
There is not like ever you come 
in connection with Kṛṣṇa consciousness,

28
00:01:44,586 --> 00:01:48,833
and then you never get 
the flu again, you know …

29
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:53,590
When Gurudev was riding 
on the train,

30
00:01:53,590 --> 00:01:56,590
he would go from
Navadvīp to Calcutta

31
00:01:56,590 --> 00:01:58,500
in service 
to Śrīla Guru Mahārāj,

32
00:01:58,500 --> 00:02:02,716
when he was
Gaurendu Brahmachārī,

33
00:02:02,966 --> 00:02:05,066
and just like people
in the modern times,

34
00:02:05,066 --> 00:02:07,566
they might say to us,
“Oh”, you know, “the Hare Kṛṣṇa;

35
00:02:07,566 --> 00:02:10,265
there was a Hare Kṛṣṇa 
on the train.”

36
00:02:10,265 --> 00:02:13,166
These are Bengalis, 
and so at that time

37
00:02:13,166 --> 00:02:17,063
they called them,
you know, ‘gaurāṅgas’.

38
00:02:17,733 --> 00:02:19,933
So, they like,
“Hey, gaurāṅga!

39
00:02:19,933 --> 00:02:23,033
We wanna talk
to the gaurāṅga.”

40
00:02:23,633 --> 00:02:26,033
And then, and they
are talking to Gurudev—

41
00:02:26,033 --> 00:02:27,633
at the time he is
Gaurendu Brahmachārī—

42
00:02:27,633 --> 00:02:30,633
and they are saying,

43
00:02:30,633 --> 00:02:34,433
“If devotees … 
they are supposed to be liberated,

44
00:02:34,433 --> 00:02:37,733
how come we see
that they get sick?

45
00:02:37,733 --> 00:02:42,013
Rather … and really they should be free
from any sort of disease

46
00:02:42,013 --> 00:02:44,533
and just always be healthy.

47
00:02:44,533 --> 00:02:47,533
You know, 
why should they be

48
00:02:47,533 --> 00:02:51,133
in an unhealthy, a diseased
condition or any such thing?”

49
00:02:51,133 --> 00:02:53,733
And Gurudev
answered by saying, he said,

50
00:02:53,733 --> 00:02:55,313
“No, just the opposite”,

51
00:02:55,313 --> 00:03:00,333
he said, “because the devotees,
they are escaping māyā,

52
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:03,433
they’re on the way out 
of the material world,

53
00:03:03,433 --> 00:03:07,783
so they should be attacked
with many varieties of things.”

